We're iterating on refactoring foff-milter, one step at a time.  Refactoring hasthis set of final goals:
1) Get rid of YAML rules in favor of rules written in rust
2) Externalize all lists into configuration files
3) Combine and simplify rules and features when possible
4) Ensure all tests pass on every iteration
5) Reduce memory usage
6) When a rule or feature needs input from a previous rule or feature, it should not use the tags themselves for that input
So for this iteration, let's analyze thoroughly and make a recommendation on what the next step should be
